text: Hurricane Bonnie was a strong Atlantic tropical cyclone in late August 1998. The storm was a major hurricane with winds near . Bonnie made landfall near Wilmington and Cape Fear, North Carolina as a strong Category 2 hurricane early on August 27. The storm also caused damage in southeastern Virginia. The storm killed five people, two directly. Damage from the storm was near $1 billion. ==References== Category:Hurricanes in the United States Category:1998 in the United States Category:August events Category:1990s in North Carolina Category:20th century in Virginia Category:1990s in weather
